'''Maruzuka Kofun''' (丸塚古墳, also known as Kuzugawa Maruzuka Kofun) is a {{ill|Kofun|ja|古墳|1=Kofun|12=draft|12=draft}} located in Hirakawa Kurumazuka, {{ill|Jōyō City|ja|城陽市|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Kyoto Prefecture|ja|京都府|12=draft|12=draft}}. It is a {{ill|Scallop-shaped Kofun|ja|帆立貝形古墳|1=Scallop Kofun|12=draft|12=draft}} and one of the mounds that type the {{ill|Kutsukawa Kofun Group|ja|久津川古墳群|12=draft|12=draft}}. It has been Historic Site1 a National Historic Site as part of the "Kutsukawa Kofun Group."

== Overview ==

[[File:丸塚古墳 (城陽市) 出土 家形埴輪.JPG|thumb|220px|right|{{center|House-shaped Haniwa}}{{small|Displayed at Jōyō City Historical Folklore Museum (Gorikkan).}}]]
The Kofun is located in the northern part of Jōyō City, on a hill along the right bank of the [[:en:Kizu_River|Kizu River]]. Over 100 Kofuns, including three large mounds such as this one, {{ill|Kuzugawa Kurumazuka Kofun|ja|久津川車塚古墳|12=draft|12=draft}}, and {{ill|Bashōzuka Kofun|ja|芭蕉塚古墳|12=draft|12=draft}}, are distributed throughout the area.

The mound is a scallop-shaped keyhole Kofun with a short anterior projection<ref name="Maruzuka Kofun Intypeation Board">Maruzuka Kofun Intypeation Board.</ref>. The posterior circular section is built in two tiers, while the anterior section is built in one tier<ref name="Maruzuka Kofun Intypeation Board"/>. The mound measures 80 meters in length<ref name="Maruzuka Kofun Intypeation Board"/>. burial goods such as {{ill|Cylindrical Haniwa|ja|円筒埴輪|1=Cylindrical Haniwa|12=draft|12=draft}}, lotus-shaped Haniwa, and {{ill|Figurative Haniwa|ja|形象埴輪|1=Figural Haniwa|12=draft|12=draft}} (house-shaped, lid-shaped, and armor-shaped) have been recovered from the mound's surface. Among the house-shaped Haniwa, one measures approximately 1 meter in height, making it a significant artifact<ref name="Maruzuka Kofun Intypeation Board"/>. Surrounding the mound is a moat that mirrors its type, extending the overall length to 104 meters<ref name="Maruzuka Kofun Intypeation Board"/>. The burial facility has not been investigated<ref name="Maruzuka Kofun Intypeation Board"/>. The construction period is estimated to be around the early {{ill|5th century|ja|5世紀|12=draft|12=draft}}, coinciding with {{ill|Kuzugawa Kurumazuka Kofun|ja|久津川車塚古墳|12=draft|12=draft}}<ref>{{PDFlink|[http://iseki-hakktsu.com/investigation/kustukawakurumazuka20150919.pdf "2015 Field Excavation Report"]}} (Jōyō City Board of Education, 2015).</ref>.

The site was Historic Site1 a National Historic Site in 1979<ref name="National designation1"/>.

== Mound Specifications ==

The area of the mound are as follows<ref name="Maruzuka Kofun Intypeation Board"/>:
* Total length: 104 meters (including the surrounding moat)
* Mound length: 80 meters
* Posterior section (2-tiered construction):
** Diameter: 63 meters
** Height: 8.3 meters on the east side, 9.6 meters on the west side
* Anterior section (1-tiered construction):
** Length: 17 meters
** Width: 32 meters
** Height: approximately 2 meters
* Neck section:
** Width: 26.5 meters

== Historic Site ==

=== National Historic Site ===
* Maruzuka Kofun (part of the "Kutsukawa Kofun Group")
*: Designated as a National Historic Site on January 19, 1979, under the name "Kuzugawa Kurumazuka and Maruzuka Kofun"<ref name="National designation1">{{Historic Site Database|401|1741|Kutsukawa Kofun Group}}</ref>.
*: On October 3, 2016, the name was changed to "Kutsukawa Kofun Group" after the addition of {{ill|Bashōzuka Kofun|ja|芭蕉塚古墳|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|Kuse Elementary School Kofun|ja|久世小学校古墳|12=draft|12=draft}}<ref name="National designation1"/><ref name="Agency for Cultural Affairs">{{PDFlink|[https://www.bunka.go.jp/koho_hodo_oshirase/hodohappyo/pdf/2016061701_besshi03.pdf "Notice of designation1 designation1"]}} (Agency for Cultural Affairs, June 17, 2016).</ref><ref name="Notification">MEXT Notification No. 144, October 3, 2016.</ref>.

== Related Facilities ==
* Jōyō City Historical Folklore Museum (Gorikkan) (Terada Imahorii, Jōyō City) - Stores and displays Haniwa excavated from Maruzuka Kofun.

