* Total length: 104 meters (including the surrounding moat)
* Mound length: 80 meters
* Posterior section (2-tiered construction):
** Diameter: 63 meters
** Height: 8.3 meters on the east side, 9.6 meters on the west side
* Anterior section (1-tiered construction):
** Length: 17 meters
** Width: 32 meters
** Height: approximately 2 meters
* Neck section:
** Width: 26.5 meters

== Historic Site ==

=== National Historic Site ===
* Maruzuka Kofun (part of the "Kutsukawa Kofun Group")
*: Designated as a National Historic Site on January 19, 1979, under the name "Kuzugawa Kurumazuka and Maruzuka Kofun"<ref name="National designation1">{{Historic Site Database|401|1741|Kutsukawa Kofun Group}}</ref>.
*: On October 3, 2016, the name was changed to "Kutsukawa Kofun Group" after the addition of {{ill|Bashōzuka Kofun|ja|芭蕉塚古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Bashōzuka Kofun|qq=}} and {{ill|Kuse Elementary School Kofun|ja|久世小学校古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kuse Elementary School Kofun|qq=}}<ref name="National designation1"/><ref name="Agency for Cultural Affairs">{{PDFlink|[https://www.bunka.go.jp/koho_hodo_oshirase/hodohappyo/pdf/2016061701_besshi03.pdf "Notice of designation1 designation1"]}} (Agency for Cultural Affairs, June 17, 2016).</ref><ref name="Notification">MEXT Notification No. 144, October 3, 2016.</ref>.

== Related Facilities ==
* Jōyō City Historical Folklore Museum (Gorikkan) (Terada Imahorii, Jōyō City) - Stores and displays Haniwa excavated from Maruzuka Kofun.

